headline: Apple’s Cook Presses Congress Over Child Online Safety Bill
summary: Apple has raised concerns about the App Store Accountability Act, which would require app stores to verify the ages of users in order to determine whether minors are using potentially harmful apps.  The House Energy and Commerce Committee is scheduled to consider the bill on Thursday morning.

headline: Talk of an AI bubble is just 'ridiculous,' this strategist says
summary: Investors are still going back and forth over whether there is an AI bubble surrounding markets (^DJI, ^IXIC, ^GSPC) or whether it is going to pop soon. One Wall Street analyst finds the chatter over the existence of an AI bubble "ridiculous." Humilis Investment Strategies CEO and Chief Investment Officer Brian Belski sits down with Market Catalysts host Julie Hyman to explain his thoughts on the AI trade, dynamic changes since the Dot-Com Bubble of the 1990s, and his view on the Magnificent Seven tech stocks. headline: How Big Tech's AI build-out is 'mostly' a private credit story

To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid. Note: Apollo Global Management is the parent company of Yahoo Finance.

headline: Sales of foreign-branded phones in China up 13.0% in October, data shows
summary: Sales of foreign-branded phones, ​including Apple Inc's ‌iPhone, increased 13.0% year-on-year in ‌China in October, according to Reuters calculations based on data released ⁠on Wednesday ‌by a government-affiliated research firm. The shipments ‍of foreign-branded phones had rose to 7.027 million units ​in October, from 6.216 ‌million handsets the same month a year earlier, calculations based on the data from the ⁠China Academy of ​Information and ​Communications Technology showed. Overall phone sales in China ‍were ⁠up 8.7% to 32.267 million units in October, ⁠according to the data.
